			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;[Please summarize the enhancement so it will be comprehensible to someone&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;from outside the Native Client team. A good summary will include:]&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
when the origin check causes a module to not load, the failure appears to 
be silent, i.e., the load appears to time out.
&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
on the off chance that HTML/nexe authors tries to host nexes on other than 
http/https, there wouldn't be any error indication.  developer confusion 
ensues.
&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
pop up some kind of alert w/ a meaningful error message.
&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
a pop up appears
&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
relatively low.  most people wouldn't try to use file/ftp/etc protocols.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-03-19T06:13:50.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-03-19T04:38:42.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>WontFix</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
